def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    clevels = [index.levels[i] for i in clocs]
    cnames = [index.names[i] for i in clocs]

    rlocs = [i for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]

    group_index = get_group_index([index.codes[i] for i in clocs], sort=False, xnull=False)

    comp_ids, obs_ids = compress_group_index(group_index, sort=False)
    recons_codes = decons_obs_group_ids(comp_ids, obs_ids, [len(x) for x in clevels], [index.codes[i] for i in clocs], xnull=False)

    new_columns = MultiIndex.from_product(clevels + [obs_ids], names=cnames + ['__placeholder__'])

    unstacked = data.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)
    unstacked.columns = new_columns

    return unstacked
